# Gushchi, Republic of Dagestan

}}
Gushchi (; ) is a rural locality (or selo) in Kubrinsky Selsoviet, Laksky District, Republic of Dagestan, Russia.
In 2010, the population was 66. There is 1 street.
Geography
Gushchi is located  southwest of the district's administrative centre Kumukh, on the Chitturdanikh river. Chitur and Kubra are the nearest rural localities.
